Michael Fennell, the President of the Commonwealth Games Federation, says that the Games will go ahead but that there "was extensive work to be done" for the 2010 Commonwealth Games in Delhi, India, ahead of its opening on 3 October. (Reuters) (Al Jazeera)Roy Halladay of the Philadelphia Phillies throws a no-hitter against the Cincinnati Reds making him the first Major League Baseball pitcher to throw a no-hitter in postseason play since Don Larsen's perfect game in the 1956 World Series. (New York Times)